## Architecture Violations

### ❌ Mistake #7: Business Logic in Controllers

```javascript
// WRONG - business logic in controller
exports.createUser = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    // Business logic should NOT be here
    if (req.body.age < 18) {
      throw new Error('Must be 18+');
    }

    const existingUser = await User.findOne({ email: req.body.email });
    if (existingUser) {
      throw new Error('Email exists');
    }

    const user = await User.create(req.body);
    res.json(user);
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
};
```

✅ **Solution**: Move business logic to services

```javascript
// CORRECT - thin controller
exports.createUser = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const user = await userService.createUser(req.body);
    res.status(201).json({ success: true, data: user });
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
};

// Business logic in service
exports.createUser = async (userData) => {
  if (userData.age < 18) {
    throw new ValidationError('User must be at least 18 years old');
  }

  const existingUser = await User.findOne({ email: userData.email });
  if (existingUser) {
    throw new ConflictError('Email already in use');
  }

  return await User.create(userData);
};
```

### ❌ Mistake #8: Direct Database Access in Controllers

```javascript
// WRONG - controller accessing database directly
exports.getUser = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const user = await User.findById(req.params.id);  // BAD!
    res.json(user);
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
};
```

✅ **Solution**: Always go through services

```javascript
// CORRECT
exports.getUser = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const user = await userService.getUserById(req.params.id);
    res.json({ success: true, data: user });
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
};
```

### ❌ Mistake #9: Routes Containing Logic

```javascript
// WRONG - logic in routes
router.post('/users', async (req, res) => {
  const user = await User.create(req.body);
  res.json(user);
});
```

✅ **Solution**: Routes should only define endpoints

```javascript
// CORRECT
router.post('/users', validate(createUserSchema), userController.createUser);
```

