## Database Access

### ❌ Mistake #10: Not Using Lean() for Read-Only Queries

```javascript
// WRONG - full Mongoose documents (slower)
const users = await User.find();
```

✅ **Solution**: Use .lean() for better performance

```javascript
// CORRECT - plain JavaScript objects (faster)
const users = await User.find().lean();
```

### ❌ Mistake #11: N+1 Query Problem

```javascript
// WRONG - N+1 queries
const posts = await Post.find();
for (const post of posts) {
  post.author = await User.findById(post.authorId);  // N queries
}
```

✅ **Solution**: Use populate or joins

```javascript
// CORRECT - single query with populate
const posts = await Post.find().populate('author', 'name email');
```

### ❌ Mistake #12: Not Handling Not Found

```javascript
// WRONG - assumes user exists
const user = await User.findById(id);
return user.name;  // Crashes if user is null
```

✅ **Solution**: Check for existence

```javascript
// CORRECT
const user = await User.findById(id);
if (!user) {
  throw new NotFoundError('User not found');
}
return user;
```

