## Validation Issues

### ❌ Mistake #16: Not Validating Input

```javascript
// WRONG - trusting user input
exports.createUser = async (req, res) => {
  const user = await User.create(req.body);  // Dangerous!
  res.json(user);
};
```

✅ **Solution**: Always validate input

```javascript
// CORRECT
router.post('/users', validate(createUserSchema), controller.createUser);

// In validator
exports.createUserSchema = [
  body('email').isEmail(),
  body('password').isLength({ min: 8 }),
  body('name').trim().notEmpty()
];
```

### ❌ Mistake #17: Client-Side Validation Only

```javascript
// WRONG - only frontend validation
// Someone can bypass your frontend validation with curl/Postman
```

✅ **Solution**: Always validate on server

```javascript
// CORRECT - validate on both client and server
router.post('/users', validate(createUserSchema), controller.createUser);
```

