## Security Problems

### ❌ Mistake #18: Storing Plain Text Passwords

```javascript
// WRONG - storing passwords in plain text
const user = await User.create({
  email: req.body.email,
  password: req.body.password  // Plain text!
});
```

✅ **Solution**: Hash passwords

```javascript
// CORRECT
const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(req.body.password, 10);
const user = await User.create({
  email: req.body.email,
  password: hashedPassword
});
```

### ❌ Mistake #19: Exposing Sensitive Data

```javascript
// WRONG - returning password in response
const user = await User.findById(id);
res.json(user);  // Includes password!
```

✅ **Solution**: Exclude sensitive fields

```javascript
// CORRECT
const user = await User.findById(id).select('-password');
res.json({ success: true, data: user });
```

### ❌ Mistake #20: SQL Injection Vulnerability

```javascript
// WRONG - string concatenation (if using SQL)
const query = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '${req.body.email}'`;
```

✅ **Solution**: Use parameterized queries or ORM

```javascript
// CORRECT - with ORM
const user = await User.findOne({ email: req.body.email });

// CORRECT - with parameterized query (if using raw SQL)
const user = await db.query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?', [req.body.email]);
```

