## Performance Issues

### ❌ Mistake #23: Not Implementing Pagination

```javascript
// WRONG - returning all records
const users = await User.find();  // Could be millions!
```

✅ **Solution**: Always paginate

```javascript
// CORRECT
const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;
const skip = (page - 1) * limit;

const [users, total] = await Promise.all([
  User.find().skip(skip).limit(limit),
  User.countDocuments()
]);

res.json({
  success: true,
  data: users,
  meta: { page, limit, total, totalPages: Math.ceil(total / limit) }
});
```

### ❌ Mistake #24: No Database Indexes

```javascript
// WRONG - slow queries without indexes
const user = await User.findOne({ email: 'test@example.com' });
```

✅ **Solution**: Add indexes

```javascript
// CORRECT - define indexes in schema
userSchema.index({ email: 1 }, { unique: true });
userSchema.index({ createdAt: -1 });
```

### ❌ Mistake #25: Loading Full Documents When Not Needed

```javascript
// WRONG - fetching all fields
const users = await User.find();
```

✅ **Solution**: Select only needed fields

```javascript
// CORRECT
const users = await User.find().select('name email').lean();
```

