## Testing Mistakes

### ❌ Mistake #26: Not Testing Error Cases

```javascript
// WRONG - only testing happy path
test('should create user', async () => {
  const user = await createUser(validData);
  expect(user).toBeDefined();
});
```

✅ **Solution**: Test error cases too

```javascript
// CORRECT
test('should throw error for invalid email', async () => {
  await expect(createUser({ email: 'invalid' }))
    .rejects
    .toThrow(ValidationError);
});
```

### ❌ Mistake #27: Not Mocking Database in Unit Tests

```javascript
// WRONG - hitting real database in unit tests
test('should create user', async () => {
  const user = await userService.createUser(data);  // Real DB call
  expect(user).toBeDefined();
});
```

✅ **Solution**: Mock database calls

```javascript
// CORRECT
jest.mock('../models/user.model');

test('should create user', async () => {
  User.create.mockResolvedValue(mockUser);
  const user = await userService.createUser(data);
  expect(user).toEqual(mockUser);
});
```

